Interquartile Range (IQR):

The IQR measures the spread of the middle 50% of the data.
To calculate the IQR:
Order the data from smallest to largest.
Find the first quartile (Q1): This is the median of the lower half of the data (25th percentile).
Find the third quartile (Q3): This is the median of the upper half of the data (75th percentile).
Subtract Q1 from Q3:
